{"questionId":"27697","questionHtml":"<p>The population of a town <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> years after 1 January 2014 can be modelled by the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>It is known that between 1 January 2014 and 1 January 2022 the population decreased by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn><mo>%</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>Use this model to estimate the population of this town on 1 January 2041.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that initial population is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15000</mn></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>15000</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>15000</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>15000</mn></math></p>\n<p>population after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn><mo>%</mo></math> decrease is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15000</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>13350</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognizing that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;on 1 January 2022 (seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitution of their value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> for 1 January 2022 and their value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced></math> into the model&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15000</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>15000</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13350</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>15000</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>014566</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitution of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2041</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2014</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>27</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and their value for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> into the model&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mn>27</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>15000</mn><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0145</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>27</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.